author: Written by: Bob Breck
title: Bob: More sunshine means warmer temps
text:
NEW ORLEANS, LA (WVUE) - After a lengthy period of cloudy skies, today saw more sunny breaks allowing temps to warm back up to near 80. This week should stay dry as no new fronts are expected before the weekend.
Highs will return to the mid to upper 80s making it feel more summer like again. The coolness of this weekend will be gone until some time next week when a stronger front is expected.
- Bob Breck
